.TH SECURE-SUDOERS-UTILS 1 "March 2026" "secure-sudoers 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
secure-sudoers-utils \- Policy, key management, and installation utilities
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B secure-sudoers-utils
.I COMMAND
[\fIARGS\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B secure-sudoers-utils
is the administrative companion to \fBsecure-sudoers\fR(1). It provides subcommands for managing cryptographic keys, signing policies, and installing the delegation framework system-wide.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B gen-keys
Generates a new Ed25519 keypair in the current directory.
.PP
.RS
Creates:
.IP \(bu 2
\fIsecure_sudoers_private_key.pem\fR (Mode 0600)
.IP \(bu 2
\fIsecure_sudoers_public_key.pem\fR (Mode 0644)
.RE
.TP
.B sign \fIPOLICY_PATH\fR \fIKEY_PATH\fR
Signs a JSON policy file with the provided private key.
.PP
.RS
Produces \fIPOLICY_PATH.sig\fR containing the raw 64-byte Ed25519 signature required by the gatekeeper.
.RE
.TP
.B update \fIURL\fR \fIPUBKEY_PATH\fR
Securely fetches and applies a policy update from a remote URL.
.PP
.RS
The URL must use HTTPS. Both the policy and its \fI.sig\fR file are fetched. The update is verified for integrity and anti-downgrade (serial check) before being atomically installed.
.RE
.TP
.B install
Installs the framework from the active policy at \fI/etc/secure-sudoers/policy.json\fR.
.PP
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Creates symlinks in \fI/usr/local/bin\fR for all delegated tools.
.IP \(bu 2
Writes a sudoers drop-in to \fI/etc/sudoers.d/secure-sudoers\fR.
.IP \(bu 2
Sets the immutable bit (\fBchattr +i\fR) on all managed files to prevent tampering.
.RE
.TP
.B unlock
Removes the immutable bit (\fBchattr -i\fR) from managed files to allow manual updates or repairs.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
An error occurred (e.g., permission denied, invalid key, network failure).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/secure-sudoers/policy.json
The active policy file used by \fBinstall\fR.
.TP
.I /etc/sudoers.d/secure-sudoers
The sudoers configuration generated by \fBinstall\fR.
.SH AUTHOR
Thomas Shephard
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR secure-sudoers (1),
.BR chattr (1),
.BR sudo (8)
